FLORAL tributes to tragic Karen Buckley have been left by the road leading to High Craigton Farm.
The occupational therapy student’s remains are believed to have been found on land to the north of Glasgow.
One passer-by left a small bouquet of flowers with the message “The rose beyond the wall” written on a card.

A 21-year-old man, who the Record understands to be Alexander Pacteau, has been arrested in connection with the death of the student, whose disappearance sparked a four-day search which ended today with the discovery of human remains.
Police Scotland said: “Officers have recovered human remains on a farm in the north Glasgow, on the outskirts of Milngavie.
“Formal identification has yet to take place, however, police believe that they may be those of missing woman Karen Buckley. Relatives are aware.
Police continue to restrict access to the area as their investigation continues.
Meanwhile, former student friends of the nurse have raised over &pound;30,000 in a day through an online gofundme page.

